            "answer_text": "Roman soldiers of equal rank grasped each other\u2019s forearms. A Roman superior officer was saluted with a right clenched fist over the heart. Roman emperors & elected magistrates were kissed on the ring of their right hand. Later Constantine gave magisterial powers to Christian bishops. That's why their rings needed to be kissed too.  ",
